MNE-led Industrialization



1. A tail of three companies


  • Tanin (Thailand)

    • Established: 1946 (electronics from 1960s)

    • Products: radio, television,

    • Out of business in latter half of 1990s

      Source: Putthiwanit (2014) http://journal.nida.ac.th/journal/upload/paper/NIDA-20150911-162843.pdf


  • Sumsung (South Korea)

    • Established in 1938 (electronics from 1960s)

    • Products: television, smart phones,

    • Became a major in 21st century

      Source: Britanica https://www.britannica.com/topic/Samsung-Electronics


  • Pensonic (Malaysia)

    • Established in 1965 (electronics from 1980s)

    • Products: lightning, refridgerator

    • Major local and (regional) brand

      Source: Companys history https://pensonic.com/about-us/our-history
